            "body": "I think @lewis6991 or @mfussenegger may have discussed something like this.\n\nBut meanwhile, `vim.filetype` is quite flexible, and `:help vim.lsp.Config` shows the current recommended way to teach Nvim about new filetypes, which can map to file extensions (and other conditions), and should thus be flexible enough to achieve a kind of \"mapping\":\n\n     vim.filetype.add({\n       filename = {\n         ['my_filename'] = 'my_filetype1',\n       },\n       pattern = {\n         ['.*/etc/my_file_pattern/.*'] = 'my_filetype2',\n       },\n     })\n     vim.lsp.config('â€¦', {\n       filetypes = { 'my_filetype1', 'my_filetype2' },\n     }\n",
